snippet.textDisplay:
The best MV for The Reve Festival Trilogy

1. Psycho
It's so classy yet there something they want to tell us. Really suit for their song storyline. It's so beautiful set with beautiful visual here. Simple yet glorious and luxury.

2. Zimzalabim
No one can do like them I guess. The MV is really eye-catching with the colourful set and its felt like we also having fun in the theme park with Red Velvet and what I like the most, the last part of MV. Totally show up hype of the song.

3. Umpah Umpah
Let me be honest, if SM do justice about the outdoor set, its gonna became totally perfect. But for the house set, I totally like to see they enjoy playing with themselves. And for beach scene, I really like the sea. But the background too obvious is just a fake background. Maybe if the doing the MV at outside as planned early, I think its gonna look more beautiful.
